This paper is about zero-shot learning for image classification, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of label attribute side information and a semantic label hierarchy, which are both related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a custom conditional random field (CRF) model, which is a common tool in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper focuses on image classification tasks, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
